For NEWS, check one of the following sources (or all):

        http://dar.linux.free.fr/
        http://sourceforge.net/projects/dar/
        http://www.99techs.net/cgi-bin/forums/yabb.pl#DARcat

You can also subscribe to the dar-news mailing-list

        http://lists.sourceforge.net/lists/listinfo/dar-news

which can be seen also throw gmane NNTP gateway:

        news://news.gmane.org/gmane.comp.sysutils.backup.dar.announce


Four mailing-lists with their corresponding newsgroup on gmane exist about DAR:

http://lists.sourceforge.net/lists/listinfo/dar-news
   for important news about dar (read-only mailing-list)

http://lists.sourceforge.net/lists/listinfo/dar-support
   for support requests. There is also the alternative of the sourceforge 
   tracker, if you prefer.

http://lists.sourceforge.net/lists/listinfo/dar-libdar_api
   a developper area around libdar and its API

http://lists.sourceforge.net/lists/listinfo/dar-discussion
   for general discussion except what concerns the technical support and 
   bug report
